      "full_name": "Khin Hlaing",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Lieutenant General Khin Hlaing has been the Commander of the Bureau of Special Operations 4 since Oct 2022. He is the former Triangle Region Commander of the Myanmar Armed Forces (Tatmadaw). He is the former Commander of the 99th Light Infantry Division (LID) and he was the Commander of the North-eastern Command of the Myanmar Armed Forces (Tatmadaw). As the Commander of the 99th LID he oversaw military operations carried out in Shan State in 2016 and early 2017. In that context, he is responsible for the atrocities and serious human rights violations committed against ethnic minority villagers in Shan State in the second half of 2016 by the 99th LID. Those include unlawful killings, forced detention and destruction of villages.",
  "birth_info": [
    {
      "date": "1968-05-02",
      "circa": false
    }
  ],
